data.title: Minneapolis StarTribune
data.meta_description: Minneapolis StarTribune - a place for remembering loved ones; a space for sharing memories, life stories, milestones, to express condolences, and celebrate life of your loved ones
data.text:
Jeffrey Glendenning

Glendenning, Jeffrey age 65, passed away August 6, 2024

Jeff is survived by sons Joshua (Tara) and Matthew, Grandson Griffin; Mother Joanne Glendenning (Bruce Hanson); Brothers Craig (Patty), Todd (Donna), Cody (LuAnn), Sister Kelli (Brad) Peterman; Many Nieces and Nephews. Preceded in death by Father Luke Wm....

Phillip Parsons

Parsons, Phillip Morris 90, of Northfield, passed away on Tuesday, August 13, 2024, while swimming at Lake Kelly-Dudley, possibly due to a medical emergency. Phillip is survived by his wife, Jean (Dzubay); children, Sue (Steve) Strachan of Bremerton, WA and Peter (Michelle) Parsons of Seattle, WA; sister, Joyce...

Robert Stabno

Stabno, Robert Charles, 80, of Isle, MN died August 12, 2024. He was born in Minneapolis, MN March 14, 1944 to parents Raymond and Leona Stabno. He married his high school sweetheart in 1965 and were together for 50 years. He raised his family in Maple Grove, MN. After 50 years in the printing industry he...

Cynthia Troendle

Troendle, Cynthia Gay, Age 82 Born August 26, 1941, Died July 15, 2024. Preceded in death by her parents Orrin Arthur and Maude Alice (Hoffman) Johnson, husband Lloyd Troendle, her brother Barry and her sons Scott and Tracy Androff.

Cindy and her husband Lloyd enjoyed riding motorcycles and gardening and feeding the...

Virginia Bandt

Bandt, Virginia (Christopherson) (90)passed away on July 23, 2024 while up at Madeline Island for a family reunion with her 3 children and their spouses, 8 grandchildren, and 4 great- grandchildren. Virginia (Ginny) was born on March 23rd, 1934 in Minot, North Dakota to Alvin and Carrie Christopherson. She...

Kristina Johnson

Johnson, Kristina "Krissy" age 29, of NE Mpls passed away on 7/31/2024 due to complications with lifelong type 1 labile diabetes. Kristina was extremely resilient, tenacious, and family oriented. She was an exceptional and devoted mother to her 3yr old son (Kaydenn). Her creativity was evident in her passions for...

Robert Juntunen

Juntunen, Robert D. Born: Sept 28, 1957 - Grand Forks, ND to parents Robert & Helen Juntunen. Died: Aug 11, 2024 - Minne-tonka, MN. Rob graduated from Grand Forks Central in 1975 and continued his education at the University of North Dakota in Electrical Engineering. He was a member of ETA Kappa Nu Association....

Beverly Westling

Beverly passed away on Monday, July 15, 2024 at the age of 78 after battling cancer. She lived in Chaska, MN for over six years before passing.

Beverly was born on May 5, 1946 in Minneapolis, MN to Helen Marr (Baker) Weinke and Herbert Marshall Weinke.

Beverly graduated from the University of Minnesota, Minneapolis...

Anne W. Grande

Anne W. Grande 8/17/2010 So much love. So little time. You live on in our hearts. Denis Peter, Emily, Gummy, Franny

Ingrid Erica White

Ingrid Erica White June 17, 1977 to August 12, 2014 Though you are no longer with us, you will never be forgotten.

Jan Boylan

Four years and still deeply missed "so much bad." Until we meet again mama, may you sing with the angels and continue to feel our love

Jill & Kelly

ELEANOR I. WALIOR

ELEANOR I. WALIOR Dec. 29, 1938 - Aug. 8, 2011 Forever in our hearts; your memories are treasured every day. Your husband, children, grandchildren, family and friends miss you

KEN "KENNY" CZUPTA

KEN "KENNY" CZUPTA Aug. 5, 1968 Aug. 20, 2006 Hi Ken, Tomorrow would be your 56th Birthday, August 5, 1968. You were actually born on a Monday. Wishing you a very Happy Birthday. Love, Love, Love You! Mom, David, Cindy, Family & Friends

Adam Engman-Delforge

Adam Engman-Delforge 8/4/80 - 3/28/03 "If I could turn back time, If I could find a way, If I could reach the stars, I'd give 'em all to you." I remember you every day, but especially on your birthday. Love you forever, Your Mother

Brian Toivonen

Brian Toivonen Happy Birthday! Love Always, Mom XOXO "May you see the reflection of your life's kindness and beauty in all the tears that fall for you." Send a kid skiing - http://Give.RidingOnInsulin.org/brian
